Title: RSA PKCS#1 v1.5 signature verification accepts malformed DigestInfo with trailing fields
Category: information-disclosure
Severity: high
Description: `lib/rsa.js` verifies RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5 signatures by ASN.1-decoding the decrypted block and checking only `obj.value[1].value` against the expected digest. It does not verify that the decoded structure is exactly a two-element `DigestInfo` sequence with the expected algorithm identifier and no trailing or extra fields. As a result, a malformed ASN.1 structure can satisfy verification as long as the second child contains the target digest, enabling signature forgery / improper verification for c
Request: Relevant code in `lib/rsa.js`:

```js
key.verify = function(digest, signature, scheme) {
  ...
  if(scheme === 'RSASSA-PKCS1-V1_5') {
    scheme = {
      verify: function(digest, d) {
        d = _decodePkcs1_v1_5(d, key, true);
        var obj = asn1.fromDer(d);
        return digest === obj.value[1].value;
      }
    };
